Thoughts on the diabetic journey... Taking care of business... and that business is US! It‚Äôs sometimes referred to as self care... but what is self care in real world terms? Some may define it as getting away for a few days to recharge, or another might define self care as following through and taking meds and seeing doctor regularly.  Self care is showing myself the same love and respect that I would show another. It may be as simple as making my bed daily, or washing the sink full of dishes, it might be checking the skin between my toes or allowing myself to say ‚Äúno‚Äù when I already have too much on my plate.  Self care is how we care for ourselves when it‚Äôs just us. It doesn‚Äôt have to be BIG it may be a small quiet something.... but we all need to practice it as a life sacrament.
